ce:section.ce:para:
In this study, N-doped CDs (N-CDs) and Mg-doped CDs (Mg-CDs) with up- and down-conversion FL were prepared by a facile and ultrafast microwave-assisted synthesis, where the synthesis completed within 2 min. The obtained CDs showed excitation-independent blue emission, and the FL QY of CDs was significantly improved after doping with Mg2+ ions. This is due to that Mg-citric acid chelate introduces Mg atom into CDs and conserves the carboxyl group, and both these effects enhance the luminescent efficiency of Mg-CDs. Furthermore, Mg-CDs could serve as superior nanoprobes for highly selective and sensitive detection of hematin based on the strong IFE between Mg-CDs and hematin (
Scheme 1
). The FL intensity ratios (I 0/I) of Mg-CDs were found to be directly proportional to the concentration of hematin in the range of 0.1–75 μM with the limit of detection (LOD) of 25 nM for Mg-CDs-0.1 and 0.01–25 μM with the LOD of 1 nM for Mg-CDs-0.5.
